description: Dimensions: EL 118.3mm; EWe 44.5; Wm; 47.3; Bm 46.4; DS 100,Typology: 3 near par. ribs - hints that they terminated in pellet.; nearly sq. body section - poss. quite crisp angles orig.; socket sub-sq. and ending in slit.,Manufacture: hints of cg. fl. in sur. only; remains of stump projecting from inner edges of mouth top - deeper broken sur. on face stretches prob. from jets,Condition: Totally blunt e. - modern interference - poss. also corr.; loop breaks gold-flecked but also prob. green corrn. traces - anc. or recent? v. large hole remaining most of rev. face - breaks coppery brown - prob. post-deposition, recent? Cracks in other face prob. anc.,Attached Material: brown and light brown soil traces
remarks: Labels/Markings: white ink inscr. 'B.56'; small rect. s/o label - printed '9' (or 6?),PIF; DF(C); SI; CI,Rec.: SN Feb 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

collection: London, Society of Antiquaries Collection, B.55
site: Unprovenanced,Alt. Site: Cornwall, St. Ives, Lelant, c. SW 53 37,Possibly one of two from the Leland hoard which should be in the Antiquaries Collection (see AFI & DF)
surface: Varied olive green - dark brown patina; scattered pocking to pale and light green dry surface.
description: Dimensions: EL 110.5mm; Wm 41.7; Bm 41.7; Blp 4.5 (min.); DS 76.1,Typology: flat mouth top, broad lips around outer edge of m. with uneven underside (with lipping) - stump of cg. fl. prob.; prob. flat rect. end; sub-rect. socket section; flat m-m with ledge under; ribs not sym. or particularly straight - gradually converging.; variable rib emphasised body angles,Manufacture: stump of cg. fl. in parts - well ground down, to form hexagonal body section; pmk between two ribs on one face - prob. flaw; not much evid. for jet stumps,Condition: all e. dam. badly - centre almost certainly anc. - yellow brown soil on break; rest rubbed/broken to dark brown,Attached Material: fawn soil in socket end; other traces in crevices, etc.
remarks: Labels/Markings: white ink inscr. B55; stuck rect. s/o label - printed '8'.,PIF; DF(C); SI; CI,Rec: SN Feb. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1
